" {\n    \"title\": \"Anagram Detection (Hard)\",\n    \"description\": \"Write a function `is_anagram` that checks if two given strings are anagrams of each other. Two words or phrases are anagrams if they contain the same letters, in any order.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef is_anagram(str1: str, str2: str) -> bool:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `str1` (str): A string containing only lowercase letters.\\n- `str2` (str): Another string containing only lowercase letters.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns `True` if the two input strings are anagrams of each other, `False` otherwise.\\n\",\n    \"code\": \"from collections import Counter\\ndef is_anagram(str1: str, str2: str) -> bool:\\n    # Create a dictionary counting the frequency of each letter in both strings\\n    count1 = Counter(str1)\\n    count2 = Counter(str2)\\n    \\n    # Check if the two dictionaries are equal (i.e., the frequencies of all letters match)\\n    return count1 == count2\",\n    \"tests\": [\n        'assert is_anagram(\"listen\", \"silent\") == True',\n        'assert is_anagram(\"hello\", \"world\") == False',\n        'assert is_anagram(\"act\", \"cat\") == True',\n        'assert is_anagram(\"example\", \"maximum\") == True'\n    ]\n}"